-------------
-- clacman --
-------------

* Required softwares *

  You will need :

  - ASDF : http://www.cliki.net/asdf
  - PAL : http://common-lisp.net/project/pal

* ASDF *

  In /usr/share/common-lisp/systems, create a symbolic link
  to the system definition file (clacman.asd)
  or
  add the ernestine directory to *central-directory* of ASDF :
  (push "/directory/clacman/" asdf:*central-registry*)

* Load *
 
  In the Lisp system :
  (asdf:operate 'asdf:load-op 'clacman)

* Launch game *

 CL-USER> (clacman:clacman)



* SBCL --script option

For people who have SBCL (>= 1.0.21), it's possible to launch the game
using  the bin/clacman.lisp  executable. Just  edit  the *clacman-dir*
and *username* parameters and :

 $> bin/clacman.lisp




